  "prompt": "What is 3E - 3 tier AC in Duronto?",
  "response": "In the context of Indian Railways, **Durunto** is a category of long-distance express trains that typically do not have any scheduled stops between the origin and destination, or very few stops. The train offers several classes of accommodation, including various types of AC (air-conditioned) coaches.\n\nWhen you see **3E - 3 tier AC** in relation to Duronto trains, it refers to **AC 3 Economy** class. Here\u2019s a breakdown of what it means:\n\n1. **3-tier (3E)**: This is a relatively new class introduced by Indian Railways to provide a more affordable option for passengers compared to the standard AC 3-tier. It has three tiers of berths (lower, middle, and upper) arranged in bays.\n\n2. **AC**: The coach is fully air-conditioned, ensuring a comfortable journey, especially in hot weather.\n\n3. **Economy**: The 3E class is designed to be a budget-friendly option. It typically has slightly fewer amenities compared to the standard AC 3-tier but still provides a comfortable and economical travel experience. The berths and space might be a bit more compact compared to regular AC 3-tier.\n\n### Key Features of 3E (AC 3 Economy) in Duronto:\n- **Berths**: Three tiers (lower, middle, and upper).\n- **Seating Arrangement**: Open bay arrangement with curtains for privacy.\n- **Air Conditioning**: Fully air-conditioned coach.\n- **Meals**: Meals are usually included in the ticket price for Duronto trains.\n- **Charging Points**: Provided for passengers to charge electronic devices.\n\nIf you\u2019re considering booking a 3E ticket on a Duronto train, it\u2019s a good option for those looking for affordable AC travel with basic comforts.",
